at.irian.ankor.path.el

Class SimpleELPathSyntax

  • java.lang.Object
    • at.irian.ankor.path.el.SimpleELPathSyntax
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PathSyntax

    public class SimpleELPathSyntax
extends java.lang.Object
implements PathSyntax
    Note: This is a very simple basic implementation that is able to handle "constant" path expressions. This implementation is NOT able to parse sophisticated nested paths like "foo[bar[5].baz['qux']]".

      • getPropertyName

        public java.lang.String getPropertyName(java.lang.String path)
        Description copied from interface: PathSyntax
        Returns the "property" of the given path. Depending on the actual path node type this can be:
        • the name of a bean property (e.g. getPropertyName("foo.bar") returns "bar")
        • an index (e.g. getPropertyName("foo.bar[5]") returns "5")
        • a literal map key (e.g. getPropertyName("foo['bar']") returns "bar")
        Specified by:
        getPropertyName in interface PathSyntax
        Returns:
        the "property" represented by the given path
